<h1>Problem 2215 - 2009 USAMO, P4 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>For \(n\geq2\) let \(a_1, a_2, \ldots a_n\) be positive real numbers such that
\[(a_1 + a_2 + \cdots + a_n)\left(\frac {1}{a_1} + \frac {1}{a_2} + \cdots + \frac {1}{a_n}\right) \leq \left(n + \frac {1}{2}\right)^2.\]
Prove that \(\max(a_1, a_2, \ldots, a_n)\leq 4\min(a_1, a_2, \ldots, a_n)\).</p>
